❯ cool will aws create ec2 and will appear in ec2 list for training or inf

⏺ Short answer: No, they won't appear in your EC2 list.

  SageMaker manages its own compute fleet completely separately from EC2. Here's what actually happens:

  Training Job (ml.m5.large)
  - AWS spins up a managed instance behind the scenes
  - It runs your container, trains, saves to S3, then terminates automatically
  - You never see it in the EC2 console
  - You can't SSH into it (unless you enable SageMaker Debugger remote access)
  - Billed per-second, only while running

  Endpoint (ml.t2.medium)
  - Same deal — managed instance, invisible to EC2
  - Stays running until you delete the endpoint
  - This is what costs ~$0.06/hr continuously

  Where you DO see them:
  SageMaker Console → Training jobs   (training instances + logs)
  SageMaker Console → Endpoints       (inference instances + metrics)
  CloudWatch        → /aws/sagemaker/TrainingJobs  (live logs)

  The practical implication for your setup: once training completes, the instance is gone automatically — no cleanup needed. But the endpoint stays running
  and billing until you explicitly delete it:

  aws sagemaker delete-endpoint \
    --endpoint-name tiny-transformer-endpoint \
    --region us-east-1

