⏺ The root cause: the inference DLC's default handler tried to load model.pt as TorchScript (torch.jit.load) and failed with constants.pkl not found because
  our model was saved as a state dict.

  The fix: at the end of training, train.py now copies inference.py and requirements.txt into SM_MODEL_DIR/code/. When SageMaker tars that directory, the
  inference container finds code/inference.py and uses our custom model_fn/predict_fn instead of the default TorchScript handler. tiktoken also gets installed
   from code/requirements.txt.

  You'll need to retrain to produce a new model.tar.gz with the bundled code.

